caption: Showed up for brunch and wasn’t served until an hour into my reservation. They also rushed me out of the table because of another incoming reservation. Service was extremely messy and not coordinated

The first time I went to Brick Lane I was blown away by the service, food, and overall atmosphere (especially considering the pandemic) they did great. The second time however was by far one of the worst experiences I have had at a restaurant. The wait staff from the point of seating my party of four was rude, inattentive (the restaurant is still at 25% capacity), and continually got our orders wrong. Now I wouldn't have been so upset if I had not observed the wait staff attending to the other patrons with far better service. It seemed as if we were only getting bad service, I am not sure what kind of business they are trying to run but they should give everyone great service no matter what.

Visited the Brick Lane for brunch recently. Had the unlimited mimosas. One of the few places in DC which serves unlimited mimosas for such great prices. We ordered the Brick Lane burger (so good!) , The French toast ( soft and not too sweet. Tasted amazing) and the Eggs Benedict ( one of the best we have had so far). The service was a little slow. The ambiance is okay. But everything gets compensated for the cheap drinks and great food. Must visit for brunch.

We came to brunch and the service was amazing! Big shout out to Ahmed! He made sure we were comfortable and had everything we need. And you can’t lose with the $20 bottomless mimosas deal. Definitely coming back!

My friends and I went on a Sunday for brunch and bottomless Mimosas. It was our first time here. We asked to be seated outside. It was not very busy when we arrived.. It took a very long time for the waiter to come take drink orders. It was suggested that our table it a full bottle of champagne and pitchers of juice since it was so many getting the bottomless drinks. The first bottle came out, the waiter opened it and poured the first drinks. The pitchers of juice were so small for it to be for a table of 5. We had to keep asking for juice which took forever to get each time. We FINALLY got to order food. The food was good even though we waited pretty long for it. We had to flag down our waiter to get more drinks. The next few bottles of champagne we had to open ourselves. After I finished I was still hungry so I ordered some fries. I NEVER GOT THEM. At this point its getting a little busy. We started noticing that our waiter was hanging out at a few tables for longer periods of time, causing us to have to get up and fund ppl to serve us. Dont want to make it about race but he definitely was giving his best service to his white customers. Anyway,  we sat for about 25mins and noone came to our table. My mom finally got up and went inside to get someone. Our waiter finally came to the table and we asked gor our checks.  Thook another 15mins to get it. When the check came i realized the fried were on the bill. I told my waiter I never got them. He snatched my bill tray from me with a little attitude. The inside of the restuarant stinks and smelled like old water under a mat. Maybe something was spilled and not cleaned up properly. Unfortunately, we will not be back. Im not sure how they got 4.3 stars.

They took their time bringing water. They took their time bringing drinks and my mimosa was warm. The food took forever, too, and it was cold. We were eating with people we'd just met, so I didn't want to make a scene. Otherwise, I'd have sent my cold potatoes and omelet back. We also ordered a well done burger to go. Got it home for my son and it was very pink inside. They aren't cooking complicated food, so it should at least be well made and hot!

Charming place. Service can be a little slow but staff are friendly. Food is ok, at reasonable prices.

Fantastic all around. I hosted a work brunch with 30 people at Brick Lane and everything went perfectly. Shannon helped coordinate the event with me weeks before, even though she was about to go into labor! We were able to agree on a very fair, customized deal in terms of pricing per person and menu options. The service itself was wonderful. The two waiters who served our group were attentive and checked on us often. The food was also great, and considering that we 30 brunch entrees ordered at once, the kitchen did a great job of getting the food out on time and I can say the quality did not suffer. I would 100% recommend this place to anyone, and will definitely be coming up.
Awesome pancakes! I was specifically looking for pancakes and that's what they delivered.

We hosted my 25th Birthday dinner at Brick Lane, and they were extremely accommodating! When I originally made the reservation, I expected around 25 people, but had to revise as 29 people in the week before the dinner. Brick Lane easily rolled with the change, and set us up for the entire top floor. They worked with us to provide drink deals, menu options, birthday shots, flexible time frame, split checks, and table setup. Everyone at my party was impressed with the rustic but luxe atmosphere, friendly service, and delicious food! I received so many compliments on choosing the venue, since the food was 10/10 even though we had so many people. The service was speedy and they were even able to split checks for everyone, which I did not expect!  Specifically about the food - I love lamb dishes and my boyfriend loves steak, but we also had some vegetarians. Everyone loved their dishes and overall, it was a great experience. I recommend this place to anyone looking for a group dinner, or even just with a friend! You really can't go wrong. Everyone working at Brick Lane cares about providing the best experience.
Great food!  Bottomless drinks and nice brunch

I ordered a Caesar salad and found a dead fly in it and here’s the funniest part of the whole situation. The bartender Omar still charged me for that salad. I didn’t say anything, I paid my bill and walked out. I live next door and I’ve heard a lot of bad things about that place and after my experience i realized that people are not lying. I completely understand the fact that it’s not the bartenders fault, but the way he ignored it was absolutely unprofessional and unacceptable. I hope you will provide some hospitality classes to your staff.
The food is amazing, and was cooked perfectly ( I had the steak) but, the atmosphere lets the place down as it can feel very quiet..
Bottomless Mimosas were wonderful food was delicious I live an hour away and I'm already planning my next trip back!!
Great food, great staff. All the makings of a good restaurant.

Fabulous neighborhood spot! We came in for dinner and ended up with the Prix Fix option which was a great deal. I had calamari which was not over battered and fresh tasting. I followed with the paella which tasted delightful and had tons of fish, the really don't skimp like some places. Additionally, we ordered a few cocktails all of which were a great deal for happy hour. While the food was great the thing that will keep me coming back is the service. I felt almost pampered by the staff and will be back.

Brick lane was an amazing experience. I met some friends here for happy hour and dinner and I cannot say enough about how wonderful of an experience it was. For starters, we all had (many) of the happy hour special drinks - the D.C. Or nothing - which is this restaurants version of a Moscow Mule. It was AMAZING, and only FIVE DOLLARS! I had.... well... I had many. My friends had the burger which they raved about and I had the salmon dinner salad which came with a really impressive piece of salmon and an equally impressive presentation/salad. I happily ate every bite. Our waiter was fantastic and while I was waiting for the bathroom the manager introduced himself to me as well. Additionally, another person (the owner perhaps?) came to our table on two occasions to ensure our food was good and we were satisfied. What phenomenal customer service! We all finished with the chocolate lava cake and creme brûlée and both were beyond excellent. If I find myself back in DC I wouldn't hesitate to return to this place. There were a number of other options on the menu I'd love to try! Don't walk, run to Brick lane!
I had a steak salad which was pretty good. My kids were unimpressed so probably not a great place for family dining. Prices are exorbitant
Came here for Sunday brunch and had an outstanding experience. Good food and better service. Thanks Patrick!
Mediocre food for brunch but very nice staff and ambience

We cancelled our order and left after 1h15 waiting for food (brunch) and drinks (2 coffees and a OJ)... the waiter didn't give us any updates and even people who arrived after us started getting their foods and drinks... horrible service!!!
Great place. Good selection, good personality.
Staff and space wonderful. Excellent mimosa at brunch. Food is average. I ordered the breakfast platter and tried brick lane burger.
Delicious bacon tomato grilled cheese
Neighborhood "Cheers" bar and restaurant with very good food.
The food was okay. The burger was average I wanted to try some of waasbi mashed potatoes but it wasn't ready
Delicious! The caprese Benedict is fantastic. Great steak and eggs too.

Food was pretty good; both the pork and chicken sandwiches were flavorful but unexceptional. Caesar salad was okay, but had too much cheese (saying this as someone who loves cheese.) Off-put by a beer menu that they only read, when they had a printed cocktail menu.
Slow service, orders were incorrect, are conditioning broken. Not a good experience. The food was fairly good, however.
I love it!! The owner is super nice, they are amazing!! The mimosas are strong, the food is amazing, & I even seen the owner give free OJ to some kids on the street! Definitely going back!
Service was great food was incredible
Great, tasty food. Tofu pad thai rocked. Reasonable prices.

The Food and Service were superb. At our table we had the Shrimp scampi, the Salmon, the coconut shrimp salad and grilled chicken. Each plate was tasty, very well cooked and presented AND above all reasonably priced. We had the Calamari for appetizer and it is was rich, nicely breaded and nice pieces. No chunks. The bar served nice drinks and any off the specialty menu r top notch...worth the $10+. They even did a superb Chocolate Vodka Martini, not on the specialty drink menu. Terrific food. Terrific drinks. Terrific Service. Altogether a dining experience WE will repeat.
Great breakfast!
Love the owner and staff! Super cute intimate restaurant with good food. Also would be a great date spot.
Food was decent, but nothing to write home about. Service was very slow and inattentive.

Nice bar and excellent food. Very relaxing atmosphere and yummy menu. Highly recommend for locals and visitors. I love brunch and dinner. Nice neighborhood bar but still welcoming to visitors. I Loved   the  scallops and my wife loved the lamb rack.
Easy, reasonable brunch and bottomless ($16 per person). Very happy!

There were only two tables inside with people so we decided to go in. They kept telling us we'd be seated soon, but it took half an hour. Waited for someone to take our drink order for 20 min. Interior is pretty cool sooo that's an upside :P
Great staff!
Terrible service at brunch. Bartender could barely tolerate any customers.

The food was actually decent, not great, but decent; however it was possibly the worst service I've ever had at a restaurant. They sat table after table and no one came to take orders. At least one table next to us got up and left after sitting for 30 minutes with no server. We finally ordered with the host after I went in and asked him. They didn't bring the coffee we asked for or one of the sides we ordered. We never got a real server and felt lucky to get our food at all.
Cute neighborhood restaurant. Recommend the eggs Benedict with avocado aioli. Socialable team.
$16 Bottomless Bloody Mary's and Mimosas on Sunday. Eggs Benedict was delicious
Great service! Great food. Great space. Great location!
Cute little spot and yummy mimosas!
Cute place and I wanted to like it. The service was not very good and everything felt pretty cramped. Good food, but not for the price. Probably won't return.

Supposedly open until midnight -  it even says so on their door - yet closed at 10:15, and some guy sitting at the bar made the "finger across the throat"  gesture  when we gave curious looks inside. Forget it, very rude,  won't try again.
Good food although the place was a little cramped for my liking

Absolutely blown away by this restaurant.  It is definitely a cozy establishment, not very large but that's not a big deal. The drinks were great and the food was out of this world for the price paid compared to other DC restaurants. Service was very friendly.
Nice staff, good food

Where do I start? This place is fantastic. I picked it because it was on a restaurant app and offered a discount on my meal if I attended. The customer service was great, including a friendly owner. The food was even better. My party had the mussels, lamb, and salmon dishes. They were fabulous and the side pairings were well thought out. I will definitely return.

Friends and I stopped into this adorable cafe for an early brunch and we were blown away by the delicious flavors of everything we ordered. We got the oatmeal with spiced apples and strawberries, crispy pancakes, the salmon and eggs benefit, and the sunrise omelet. Every single dish was absolutely delectable. I wish I was a local so I could come back and try lunch and dinner!
cute restaurant, good brunch
Absolutely loved this place! Had a Sun Rise Omelette and Creme Brulee and they were so good. Music, staff and interior were nice too.
Tasty food, nice trendy interior, and nice staff. I would go again!

Brick Lane has a great location, tasty versions of well loved dishes, reasonable prices, and a great staff who get to know you by name. I always enjoy my decision to stop in for a drink and some great food after work or during brunch hours on the weekends!
Really great food & nice vibe. A wonderful addition to the neighborhood.
One star is too much.  One of the worst services I have ever had. Walked out after 15 min with only water to drink.
Best new restaurant in DC!!!!!!

I'm a big fan of this new restaurant near Dupont circle.  It's a very nice place with an upscale feel.  They have great vegetarian and fish options for me.  My favorites are the Pad Thai with a nice filet of Salmon on top, and the PORTOBELLO MUSHROOM SANDWICH is out of this world.  I come back almost once a week.

Our first time here and it was amazing!  We came during brunch and had the mimosas and build your own omlet. BEST omlet I've ever had by the way! Service (bartender)  was amazing and the resturant was super clean and really nicely decorated. Deff would come here again !

The food was amazing!! Both my vegetarian and carnivorous friends thoroughly enjoyed themselves! From the fabulous ambiance and service to the delicious food and drink, a great time was had by all!!! I highly recommend this establishment!!
Excellent food every time I've eaten here, especially salmon!  Drinks are good, with nice selection of wines.  Great new classy addition to the area.
Fantastic meal with excellent service!!
The rack of lamb is excellent.

It is disappointing for a new restaurant in such a vibrant neighborhood to miss on the details. For a newly opened restaurant to have chipped plates and badly painted chairs and tables, they are either used or badly handle. Except the salads, the three dishes we ordered were either semi cooked earlier or made of low quality ingredients. The fruits and vegetables used for garnishing were clearly old and the taste was less than okay. The sausages tasted like they were cooked a couple of days earlier. We ordered a couple of deserts. The chocolate lava cake was okay but a bit sweeter than it should be, but the crème brûlée was old and dry pudding with freshly burned sugar.  What a disappointment!

As someone who lives in the neighborhood, I was looking forward to the opening of a new restaurant right around the corner. It did not disappoint. The service was incredible and the food rivaled the service. I got a vegetarian tofu dish that was absolutely delicious (and huge). My boyfriend got the Hanger Steak which was amazing (the highlight was the wasabi mashed potatoes) and well worth the cost. Secretly, we were both going to the restaurant because we saw lava cake on the menu and couldn't resist. We got two. Zero regrets, it was great. I highly recommend due to good food and good service. Eat local!
